<Layout 
  title="Products People Actually Want | Anton Sten – UX Lead & Product Designer"
  description="A Designer's Guide to Building Better. Learn how to create products people love, with practical frameworks, real-world advice, and 25+ years of experience."
  path="/books/products-people-actually-wants"
>
  <div class="max-w-[700px] mx-auto px-8 sm:px-6 mt-[20vh]">
    <h1 class="text-black font-medium text-[48px] leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.02em] sm:text-display mb-20">Products People Actually Want</h1>
    <h2 class="body-xxl mb-12 font-semibold">A Designer's Guide to Building Better</h2>
    <p class="body-xxl mb-12">The world is full of products nobody wants. Here's how to build the ones they do.</p>
    <OptimizedImage 
      src="/images/products-people-actually-wants-cover.webp" 
      alt="Products People Actually Want book cover" 
      className="w-full mb-20" 
    />
    <p class="body-xxl mb-12">Every day, thousands of new apps and websites launch. Most will disappear within months. The few that survive often frustrate users more than they help them.</p>
    <p class="body-xxl mb-12">But some products feel different. They solve real problems, respect people's time, and create moments of genuine delight. Users don't just tolerate them—they advocate for them.</p>
    <p class="body-xxl mb-20">What's the difference? <br><strong>The teams behind great products understand that design isn't just about interfaces—it's about humans.</strong></p>
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 mb-20">
      <a href="#free-chapter" class="inline-block text-center px-4 py-2 bg-green text-white rounded-[4px] hover:bg-green/90 transition-colors text-[16px] leading-[24px] tracking-[-0.01em] font-medium">Download free chapter</a>
      <a href="#buy" class="inline-block text-center px-4 py-2 bg-black text-white rounded-[4px] hover:bg-black/90 transition-colors text-[16px] leading-[24px] tracking-[-0.01em] font-medium">Get the full book</a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-12">What You'll Learn</h2>
    <div class="space-y-8 mb-20">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Part 1: Foundations</h3>
        <p>Master the fundamentals of product design and understand why user experience affects every part of your business.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Part 2: Building Your Practice</h3>
        <p>From solo designer to design leader—practical advice for growing your career and managing teams.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Part 3: The Craft</h3>
        <p>Dive deep into design processes, principles, and systems that separate good designers from great ones.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Part 4: Communication & Influence</h3>
        <p>Learn to sell your ideas, influence stakeholders, and bridge the gap between design and business.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Part 5: Designing for Humans</h3>
        <p>Go beyond functional to create experiences that truly serve people's deeper needs and emotions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-12">"This isn't just another design book"</h2>
    <p class="mb-8">Unlike books that focus on theory or specific tools, <em>Products People Actually Want</em> gives you a complete framework for thinking about design—from understanding business constraints to creating emotionally resonant experiences.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-lg text-black/90 mb-20">
      <li><strong>Why some products succeed while others fail</strong> (it's not what you think)</li>
      <li><strong>How to balance user needs with business goals</strong> without compromising either</li>
      <li><strong>The communication skills that separate good designers from great ones</strong></li>
      <li><strong>How to design for real humans in real situations</strong> (not perfect users in perfect conditions)</li>
      <li><strong>Practical frameworks you can use immediately</strong> in your current work</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-12">About the Author</h2>
    <OptimizedImage 
      src="/images/anton.jpg" 
      alt="Anton Sten" 
      className="w-32 h-32 rounded-full mx-auto mb-8" 
    />
    <h3 class="body-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-center">Anton Sten</h3>
    <p class="body-lg text-black/70 mb-2 text-center">UX Lead & Product Designer</p>
    <p class="body-lg text-black/80 mb-8 text-center">With over 25 years of experience, Anton has consulted for IKEA, Herman Miller, Loom, Google, Spotify, and is Head of Design at Summer Health. His writing is featured across the design community, and he's a regular speaker at conferences and design schools worldwide. Based in Sweden, Anton divides his time between designing products that matter, writing about the craft of design, and long walks with his dog Taylor.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-12 text-center">What readers are saying</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-8 mb-20">
      <li class="text-lg text-black/90 italic">"Finally, a book that connects design thinking to real business outcomes. Anton's insights about the human side of design are game-changing."</li>
      <li class="text-lg text-black/90 italic">"This should be required reading for anyone building digital products. Practical, honest, and immediately actionable."</li>
      <li class="text-lg text-black/90 italic">"Anton doesn't just tell you what to do—he shows you why it matters. The chapter on designing for humans alone is worth the price."</li>
    </ul>

